[SN]TITLE[SN]
Teenager arrested after Despenser Gardens 'knife attack'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 17-year-old boy has been arrested after an alleged knife attack which left two men in hospital.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Police said the victims managed to call 999 after getting to a petrol station in Tudor Street, Riverside, following an assault in nearby Despenser Gardens.
Both men were taken to hospital following the incident which happened at about 19:00 BST on Friday.
One man remains in hospital in a stable condition while the other has been discharged.
